European stock-index futures
extended their decline as Moody’s Investors Service downgraded  Spain ’s credit rating to Aa2. Futures on the Euro Stoxx 50 Index
expiring this month slid 1.1 percent to 2,902 at 7:17 a.m. in  London .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
